---
// WhyThisMatters.astro
// Why bounded disclosure matters
---

<section class="section section--alt reveal" id="why">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="why-content">
      <h2>Why This Matters</h2>
      <p>
        People already share deeply personal context with AI systems &mdash; health
        concerns, financial anxieties, private doubts, relationship problems,
        strategic intentions.
      </p>
      <p>
        The next step is agents acting on that context and coordinating directly
        with each other.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can try to make that safer by stripping away context before they
        coordinate. But context-free agents can only do shallow work.
      </p>
      <p>
        The more useful path is to let agents coordinate with context while
        putting hard limits on what can leave the interaction.
      </p>
      <p class="why-content__emphasis">
        AgentVault makes that boundary mechanical rather than social, and
        verifiable rather than assumed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why-content {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .why-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .why-content p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .why-content__emphasis {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
